<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>HEAT VENTILATION AIR CONDITIONING (HVAC), Orifice Tube System, Pre-March 2007 - 3200, 4100, 4200, 4300,
        4400, 7300, 7400, 7500, 7600, 7700, 8500, 8600 - REMOVE AND INSTALL - HVAC CONTROL PANEL ASSEMBLY
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc id="hl1602521" svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="1">
        <title>HVAC CONTROL PANEL ASSEMBLY</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Refer to
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f1602535">Figure 36</hotlnk>
                        while performing the following steps.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Remove</title>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>Place the ignition key in the OFF position before removing or installing the HVAC control
                        panel assembly.
                    </para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">The trim plate is secured by five spring clips. Carefully pry the trim plate (1) from
                    the center section of the IP.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove four screws securing HVAC control panel assembly (2) to IP.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1602535" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg16/G1602535.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="472px"
                         scalefitheight="312px"/>
                <caption>Figure 36. HVAC Control Panel Assembly</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove control panel assembly from instrument panel by pulling it straight out of its IP
                    mounting cavity.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect wiring connector from rear of HVAC control panel.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Install</title>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>Place the ignition key in the OFF position before removing or installing the HVAC control
                        panel assembly.
                    </para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Connect wiring connector to rear of HVAC control panel (2).</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">With HVAC control panel assembly correctly oriented, insert it straight into the IP
                    mounting cavity.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Verify that the control panel assembly is fully seated, then secure the assembly using
                    four screws.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the trim plate (1) in the center section of the IP by aligning the spring clips
                    and carefully pressing the trim plate into position.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
